{"source_hash": "5dcf01c6aeb945ce", "candidate": {"id": "cand-007", "name": "Marco Bellini", "raw_cv": "MARCO BELLINI\nmarco.bellini@email.com | Milan, Italy (Remote)\n\nSENIOR DATA ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nData engineer with 5 years of experience building cloud-native data pipelines for financial services clients across Europe. Expert in Python, dbt, and Snowflake. Strong background in event-driven architectures. Available for remote roles only.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Data Engineer \u2014 Mediobanca (Remote) (2021\u2013present)\n- Built real-time risk data pipelines using Python, Kafka, and dbt on Snowflake\n- Designed a multi-tenant data model for regulatory reporting across 5 European subsidiaries\n- Introduced automated data quality checks using Great Expectations\n\nData Engineer \u2014 Nexi Payments, Milan (2019\u20132021)\n- Developed payment processing data pipelines in Python and BigQuery\n- Built Airflow DAGs for daily reconciliation jobs\n\nSKILLS\nPython, SQL, dbt, Snowflake, BigQuery, Kafka, Airflow, Great Expectations, Docker, Terraform\n\nEDUCATION\nMSc Data Science \u2014 Politecnico di Milano (2017\u20132019)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nEU citizen \u2014 would require UK work visa sponsorship to work in the UK", "raw_linkedin": "Senior data engineer building data platforms for European fintech and banking clients. Five years of experience with Python, dbt, and Kafka. Currently working fully remote for Mediobanca from Milan. I've worked across risk data, payments reconciliation, and regulatory reporting \u2014 environments where accuracy is non-negotiable. Open to senior remote data engineering roles at ambitious companies. Not interested in relocation; I work remotely by choice and have built my life and routines around it.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Marco, thanks for joining. You're based in Milan \u2014 can you tell me more about your working arrangement?\n\nMarco: Yes, I've been fully remote since 2020. My current role at Mediobanca is 100% remote \u2014 I work from my home office in Milan. That's a non-negotiable for me at this stage of my life. My partner works here, we have a house here. I wouldn't relocate to London, and I can't commit to being physically present in an office.\n\nInterviewer: Our role requires five days a week at Canary Wharf in London. That would be a hard requirement.\n\nMarco: I see. That's unfortunately not something I can do. I was perhaps not fully clear on that when I applied. I'm only looking at fully remote positions. I can do occasional travel to a client site \u2014 maybe a week here and there \u2014 but daily office attendance in another country isn't possible for me.\n\nInterviewer: I understand. Would you need visa sponsorship to work in the UK if there were ever a remote arrangement?\n\nMarco: Yes, as an EU national post-Brexit I would need a UK work visa. But as I said, remote is my only option. I hope I haven't wasted your time.\n\nInterviewer: Not at all, we appreciate your honesty. The technical profile is excellent; it's just the location constraint. Let me note that for our records.", "years_experience": 5.0, "skills": ["Python", "SQL", "dbt", "Snowflake", "BigQuery", "Kafka", "Airflow", "Great Expectations", "Docker", "Terraform"], "industries": ["financial services", "fintech", "banking", "payments"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.9, "culture_fit_score": 0.85, "constraints": [{"id": "84624911", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Requires fully remote working; will not work in office. Non-negotiable.", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 0.0, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "fa730885", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Fully remote working is a non-negotiable requirement.", "canonical_key": "remote_ok", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "9b302b10", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "EU citizen post-Brexit; requires UK work visa sponsorship to work in the UK.", "canonical_key": "visa_sponsorship", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.97}, {"id": "4b24ca00", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Will not relocate; has family and established life in Milan.", "canonical_key": "relocation_required", "value": false, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98}, {"id": "c52b6edc", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_arrangement", "description": "Open to occasional travel to client sites (a week here and there), but cannot commit to regular office presence.", "canonical_key": "travel_percent", "value": 5.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 0.7, "confidence": 0.85}]}, "embedding": [-0.04887651652097702, 0.004732530098408461, 0.06846392899751663, 0.007322275545448065, -0.026541605591773987, -0.030866611748933792, -0.004555060062557459, 0.057211026549339294, -0.016603292897343636, -0.03231266140937805, -0.006043835077434778, -0.029446853324770927, -0.02500353381037712, -0.0013638888485729694, 0.03460005298256874, 0.0944402664899826, -0.03252299875020981, 0.0010845380602404475, -0.03544139117002487, 0.011147737503051758, 0.02136211469769478, 0.04858730733394623, -0.041278176009655, 0.017273733392357826, 0.002047476591542363, -0.015801390632987022, -0.0524522066116333, 0.032286372035741806, 0.03509959578514099, -0.022006263956427574, 0.031891994178295135, -0.03838607668876648, -0.007591766770929098, 0.016879357397556305, 0.007236827164888382, 0.015065220184624195, 0.028132261708378792, 0.04296085610985756, 0.015288700349628925, -0.019337642937898636, -0.044222861528396606, -0.0206390880048275, 0.03268074989318848, 0.032286372035741806, -0.022190306335687637, 0.023005353286862373, -0.02631812542